## Typography — Apple system faces

- `--font-sans` SF Pro → `-apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, system-ui, …` (UI)
- `--font-rounded` SF Pro Rounded → `ui-rounded, …` (day numerals — tabular)
- `--font-mono` SF Mono → `ui-monospace, SFMono-Regular, Menlo, …` (times, week numbers — tabular)

Compact scale (it's a menu-bar surface): large-title 26 · title 22 · **title2 17 semibold** (panel month header) · title3 15 · headline/body 13 · callout 12 · subheadline 11 · footnote/caption 10 · micro 7. Weights 400/500/600/700. Uppercase weekday headers get `letter-spacing: 0.04em`.

> ⚠️ Fonts are Apple system keywords — real SF on macOS, platform-sans fallback elsewhere. No webfont files ship. Don't substitute a different family without asking; for pixel-faithful off-Mac rendering, supply licensed SF `@font-face` files.

---

## Geometry, depth, motion

- **Spacing** 4pt scale: 4 / 8 / 12 / 16 / 20 / 24 / 32. Panel padding 16.
- **Radii — continuous (squircle) corners.** controls 8 · cards 10 · panel & sheets 14 · chip 4 · capsule 999. Day cell 8.
- **Materials.** Panel & sheets use `regularMaterial`: `backdrop-filter: saturate(180%) blur(20px)` + inset hairline. Transparency only on floating chrome (panel, command bar, agenda headers) — never dense content. Solid fallback = opaque panel surface.
- **Cards = hairline border (6%) + low fill (4%)**, not a heavy shadow.
- **Elevation (cool).** panel `0 4px 12px rgba(0,0,0,.12)` glass / `.06` solid · sheet `0 12px 40px rgba(0,0,0,.22)` · join button accent glow `0 3px 8px rgba(51,115,242,.22)`.
- **Motion — two springs.** snappy `cubic-bezier(.22,1,.36,1)` ~200ms (hover, selection); smooth `cubic-bezier(.4,0,.2,1)` ~220ms (expand/disclose). Press scales to 0.97; join button lifts to 1.01. Always gate on `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- **States.** hover fill 4→8% · press 10% · row hairline fades in on hover · selected = accent tint + 55% ring · disabled = 0.5 opacity.

**Signature element — the DayCell:** today is a filled accent circle with a white SF-Rounded numeral; selection is an accent ring over a soft fill; events show as up to three overlapping calendar-colored dots (+N overflow).

