## Content & voice

Terse, functional, native-macOS — labels and short imperatives, no personality, no marketing.
- **Title Case** for actions/menus/buttons: *New Event · Go to Today · Join Meeting · Link Plaud recording…* **Sentence case** for subtitles: *"Open Equinox when you sign in."*
- Surface **keyboard shortcuts inline** with padded spacing: *"New Event   ⌘N"*, *"Go to Today   T"*, *"Pin Equinox   P"*.
- **24-hour time**, en-dash range *"09:00 – 10:00"*; short relative cues *"in 10 min" / "now"*. Section headers: *Today / Tomorrow*, else *"Nov 18"* + short weekday.
- RSVP: *Accept · Maybe · Decline*; pending shows a *Respond* badge.
- Empty states quiet: *"No upcoming events."* Errors direct & actionable: *"No writable calendars available. Check Calendar access in Privacy settings."*
- `…` marks actions that open more UI. **No emoji. No exclamation marks. No adjectives.**

---

## Iconography

App uses **Apple SF Symbols**, hierarchical ~1.5–2px stroke (chevron.left/right, calendar, plus, pin/pin.fill, ellipsis, xmark, clock, mappin, video.fill, person.2.fill, waveform, gearshape, paintpalette). Menu-bar date badge is a **template image** in three styles (minimal filled-knockout / classic stroked / compact plain), optionally prefixed by a meeting-camera glyph. Provider glyphs: Zoom→video, Teams→person.2, Chime→phone.

> ⚠️ SF Symbols are proprietary and can't ship to the web. Substitute **Lucide** (nearest stroke match) — the design system draws them inline in `components/core/Icon.jsx` (no CDN). Use Lucide for any web target; keep SF Symbols only in Mac-native code.

---

## Components (React, via `window.EquinoxDesignSystem_262896`)

- **core** — `Icon`, `Button` (prominent / bordered / plain / destructive; regular/small), `IconButton` (square toolbar, `selected` ring), `Card` (secondary/subtle/raised), `Badge`, `Chip` (calendar dot + label), `Toggle`, `Segmented`.
- **calendar** — `DayCell` (today/selected/dots/boundaries), `EventCard` (agenda row: spine + mono time + title + inline join), `AgendaHeader`, `MenuBarPill`.
- **events** — `RSVPBar` (Accept/Maybe/Decline), `JoinButton` (accent-gradient meeting CTA), `MetadataRow` (icon-circle + label/value), `StatusChip`, `Banner` (error/warning).

One prominent button per view. Compose kits from these primitives — don't re-implement them.

---

## Do / Don't

**Do:** one accent; cool blue-grey glass; continuous corners; hairline-on-low-fill cards; SF type with rounded numerals + mono times; Title-Case terse copy; snappy/smooth motion; respect light & dark via `:root[data-theme="dark"]`.

**Don't:** add a second brand color; use gradients on content (only the dark celestial desktop + the join button); use emoji; use heavy drop shadows; use generic fonts (Inter/Roboto); write chatty marketing copy; hand-roll SF Symbols as emoji or crude SVG — use the Lucide set.
